Reasoning: The paper presents an efficient distributed memory parallel algorithm for computing connected components in undirected graphs. This involves techniques for load balancing and reducing communication volume, which are typical concerns in distributed computing. The paper also discusses the efficiency of the algorithm for different graph topologies, which suggests a focus on graph theory and algorithms. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Other possible sub-categories include cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), which are relevant to the study of graph connectivity and its applications in various domains.
